---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="AI Consulting – Onyx Labs"
  description="Clarity on what to build — and why."
>
  <section class="content-main">
    <div class="container shell">
      <div class="content-layout">
        <div>
          <h1 class="content-heading">Clarity on what to build — and why.</h1>
          <p class="content-lede">
            We work with founders, product leaders, and technical teams to identify where AI
            meaningfully moves the needle, then chart a path from prototype to production.
          </p>
          <div class="content-tags">
            <span class="tag">AI Strategy</span>
            <span class="tag">Use-case Discovery</span>
            <span class="tag">Roadmapping</span>
            <span class="tag">Technical Due Diligence</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <aside class="content-panel">
          <h3>Typical questions we answer</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Where does AI create real leverage in our product?</li>
            <li>Should we build on APIs, open models, or our own stack?</li>
            <li>How do we sequence our AI roadmap across teams?</li>
            <li>What's the right level of investment this year?</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>

      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="content-panel">
          <h3>Strategy & roadmap</h3>
          <p>
            We run structured discovery across your product, operations, and data to find the
            highest-impact AI opportunities and stack-rank them by value, risk, and complexity.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Opportunity mapping across product and operations.</li>
            <li>North-star narratives for key AI capabilities.</li>
            <li>Sequenced roadmap aligned to constraints and risk.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="content-panel">
          <h3>Architecture & vendor decisions</h3>
          <p>
            We help you choose the right mix of vendors, models, and internal capabilities, with
            clear trade-offs documented for leadership and engineering.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Architecture options from API-first to self-hosted.</li>
            <li>Evaluation criteria for models and platforms.</li>
            <li>Build vs. buy recommendations with rationale.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-section">
        <div class="section-header flex justify-between align-items-start flex-wrap gap-3 mb-3">
          <div>
            <div class="section-title">Ways to work together</div>
            <p class="section-subtitle mb-0">
              From one-off deep dives to ongoing advisory as your AI program matures.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-grid">
          <div class="card-onyx">
            <div class="card-label">Advisory</div>
            <div class="card-title">Ongoing AI advisor</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              A dedicated advisor who joins strategy, product, and architecture conversations as
              your AI program evolves.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-onyx">
            <div class="card-label">Intensive</div>
            <div class="card-title">AI opportunity sprint</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              A focused 2–3 week engagement to identify, stress-test, and prioritize your highest
              value AI bets.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-onyx">
            <div class="card-label">Review</div>
            <div class="card-title">Architecture & vendor review</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              Independent review of your planned stack, with concrete recommendations and
              trade-offs.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
